ted node(s): activate to sort column ascending\" class=\"entry sorting\" colspan=\"1\" id=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; border-top-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; height: 0px; width: 281.484px;\"><div class=\"dataTables_sizing\" style=\"height: 0px; overflow: hidden;\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Selected node(s)</strong></div></th></tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row odd\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.u-switch</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__2\">Widget node</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.u-switch.checked</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__2\">Widget node when the widget is checked</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.u-switch.u-invalid</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__2\">Widget node when the value is invalid</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.u-switch.u-format-invalid</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__2\">Widget node when there is format invalid</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.u-switch.readonly</code> or\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">.u-switch[readonly]</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__2\">Widget node when the widget is read-only</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.u-switch.disabled</code> or\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">.u-switch[disabled]</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__2\">Widget node when the widget is disabled</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.u-switch:hover</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__2\">Widget node when the widget is hovered</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.u-switch:active</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__2\">Widget node when the widget is active</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.u-switch:focus</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__2\">Widget node when the widget has focus</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.u-switch:focus-visible</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__2\">Widget node when the widget has focus-visible</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.u-switch::part(label)</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__2\">Label node</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.u-switch::part(switch)</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__2\">Switch node</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.u-switch::part(status-message)</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__2\">Status message node<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"kin1709198869557__note_nln_t3m_lfc\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> You can apply the\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">order</code> CSS style property to this node\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tto rearrange the position of a status message (both checked\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tand unchecked) with respect to other\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\telements.</div></td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.u-switch::part(switch-toggle)</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__2\">Switch toggle node</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.u-switch::part(checked-message)</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__2\">Checked message node</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.u-switch::part(unchecked-message)</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__2\">Unchecked message node</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.u-switch::part(error)</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__2\">Error node</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.u-switch .u-checked-message</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__2\">Checked message text node</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.u-switch .u-unchecked-message</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__2\">Unchecked message text node</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.u-switch .u-label-text</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__2\">Label text node</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.u-switch .u-error-icon</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__2\">Error icon node</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.u-switch:has(.u-checked-message:not(:empty))::part(status-message)</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__2\">Status message node when a checked message is defined.<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"kin1709198869557__note_hkz_kjm_lfc\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The reserved width defined for a\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tchecked message can be applied to this node. The default\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\twidth applied is 12ch.</div></td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.u-switch:has(.u-unchecked-message:not(:empty))::part(status-message)</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"kin1709198869557__table_fmd_rjl_q1c__entry__2\">Status message node when an unchecked message is\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tdefined.<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"kin1709198869557__note_ugz_1tm_lfc\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The reserved width\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tdefined for an unchecked message can be applied to this\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tnode. The default width applied is 12ch.</div></td>\n</tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"dataTables_scrollFoot\" style=\"overflow: hidden; border: 0px; width: 100%;\"><div class=\"dataTables_scrollFootInner\"><table class=\"table dataTable no-footer\" count-columns=\"2\" style=\"margin-left: 0px;\"><tfoot></tfoot></table></div></div></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kin1709198869557__section_ukv_nwn_jgc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d313186e618\">Widget sources</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The widget source files, such as JavaScript and CSS files, can be downloaded from the\n\t\t\t\tfollowing GitHub repository: <a class=\"xref\" href=\"https://github.com/RocketSoftware/uniface-ux/tree/main/src/ux/switch\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/RocketSoftware/uniface-ux/tree/main/src/ux/switch</a>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/goa1709705635907.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ux-Switch</a><p>This section provides description for the logical UX widget ux-Switch properties.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lzi1701171069984.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>UX Widgets</a><p>Uniface UX provides a set of widgets that are implemented using the UX Widget Interface. This set is referred as UX Widgets. The sources of these widgets are available and allow changes and/or extensions to the widgets. In a default Uniface installation, you can find the sources in the &lt;install&gt;\\uniface\\webapps\\uniface\\common\\ux folder.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_6399023\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_6399023\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "uxswitch Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 12, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 The uxswitch widget is a toggle field control. It always contains a field value, even if it is not a valid Boolean. Unlike the checkbox widget, the uxswitch widget does not provide the indeterminate state, so null value or empty (\"\") value results in a format error. Default Logical Widgets The default logical widget is ux-Switch . Triggers (web)trigger onchange : This trigger is fired when the uxswitch value is changed. Extends fluent-switch Web Component This widget is implemented using the Fluent web component fluent-switch. Most of its features are also available in this widget. Most of its events are mapped to triggers. For more information, see the Fluent documentation on the fluent-switch web component. Keyboard support When widget has focus, pressing the Spacebar key toggles the widget state. Layout processing Widget class method processLayout() constructs the template HTML for this widget. It generates nodes for the control itself as well as slots for label, checked-message, unchecked-message and error icon, and returns it to Uniface. Use this function to enhance the widget with more static features. Widget properties The uxswitch widget supports the following properties: Table 1. Widget Properties Property Description html:title Defines a hover over text or tooltip, currently used as helper text. html:disabled Defines the widget as being disabled. html:readonly Defines the widget as being read-only. html:hidden Defines a boolean value that hides or shows a switch. html:tabindex Allows or prevents a field from getting sequential focus usually with the Tab key. class:classname Boolean value that adds or removes a specified class. label-text Defines the label text. label-position Defines the position of the label with respect to its widget. The available options are: before (default) after Note: If the label-position is not defined for the widget, it is aligned by default before the widget. unchecked-message Defines a message for an unchecked state. checked-message Defines a message for a checked state. exclude Defines that there will be no column for the field in the uxdatagrid . Note: This is actually not a widget property. It is a field property, used by the uxdatagrid widget if that is the containing entity's widget. Helper and validation error visualization A uxswitch deals with the following error visualizations: Red color border and outline alert Alert icon Tool-tip when hovering the alert icon showing the error message When the widget is in an error state, the checked/unchecked message slot is changed to display the invalid state. By toggling the error is resolved. The error is not brought back by toggling back. UI blocking When the field is in transaction, the uxswitch widget blocks user input by becoming read-only. Widget styling Search: Column CSS Selector Selected node(s) Filter results... 23 rows found Export to Excel Export to CSV CSS Selector Selected node(s) Filter 23 rows found Filter 23 rows found CSS Selector Selected node(s) .u-switch Widget node .u-switch.checked Widget node when the widget is checked .u-switch.u-invalid Widget node when the value is invalid .u-switch.u-format-invalid Widget node when there is format invalid .u-switch.readonly or .u-switch[readonly] Widget node when the widget is read-only .u-switch.disabled or .u-switch[disabled] Widget node when the widget is disabled .u-switch:hover Widget node when the widget is hovered .u-switch:active Widget node when the widget is active .u-switch:focus Widget node when the widget has focus .u-switch:focus-visible Widget node when the widget has focus-visible .u-switch::part(label) Label node .u-switch::part(switch) Switch node .u-switch::part(status-message) Status message node Note: You can apply the order CSS style property to this node to rearrange the position of a status message (both checked and unchecked) with respect to other elements. .u-switch::part(switch-toggle) Switch toggle node .u-switch::part(checked-message) Checked message node .u-switch::part(unchecked-message) Unchecked message node .u-switch::part(error) Error node .u-switch .u-checked-message Checked message text node .u-switch .u-unchecked-message Unchecked message text node .u-switch .u-label-text Label text node .u-switch .u-error-icon Error icon node .u-switch:has(.u-checked-message:not(:empty))::part(status-message) Status message node when a checked message is defined. Note: The reserved width defined for a checked message can be applied to this node. The default width applied is 12ch. .u-switch:has(.u-unchecked-message:not(:empty))::part(status-message) Status message node when an unchecked message is defined. Note: The reserved width defined for an unchecked message can be applied to this node. The default width applied is 12ch. Widget sources The widget source files, such as JavaScript and CSS files, can be downloaded from the following GitHub repository: https://github.com/RocketSoftware/uniface-ux/tree/main/src/ux/switch . Related Links ux-Switch This section provides description for the logical UX widget ux-Switch properties. UX Widgets Uniface UX provides a set of widgets that are implemented using the UX Widget Interface. This set is referred as UX Widgets. The sources of these widgets are available and allow changes and/or extensions to the widgets. In a default Uniface installation, you can find the sources in the <install>\\uniface\\webapps\\uniface\\common\\ux folder. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}